\keepn \cf0 \f1\fs48 {\uldb \{bml ELEFILE.BMP\}}{\v Topic28}\qc Bool - Dialog\par\pard\tx360\ql \f0\fs24 \{bmc BOOLDLG.SHG\}\par
The In-/Output functions is programmed in a script.\par
The language is the Boolean Algebra.\par
\par
A line has the following format:\par
term = variable  Warning: no input is allowed here.\par
Variable: xxR - xx is a two-digit hexadecimal number, R is a register\par
There are four registers:\par
e or i \tab input\par
a or o \tab output\par
z or s \tab state\par
m \tab memory\par
If you write a register name with big letters, the negative conents is returned.\par
In a assignment, a register name can also be written with big letters. This has no effects.\par
\par
The term:\par
f \tab constant for false\par
w or t \tab constant for true\par
Term- or Term! \tab negation, corresponds to NOT(Term)\par
Term op VarKonst \tab a two-digit operator, corresponds to (Term) op VarKonst\par
+ oder | \tab logical OR\par
* oder & \tab logical AND\par
@ \tab negated OR or NOR\par
\'A7 \tab negated AND or NAND\par
x oder \'5E \tab exclusive OR resp. antivalence or XOR\par
> \tab implikation =>\par
< \tab implikation <=\par
~ \tab equivalence <=>\par
operands, that are represented by letters, can also be represented by the corresponing big letters.\par
A comment starts with a slash (/) . Everything after the slash is ignored.\par
If you confirm the dialog box with OK, a syntax check is done before closing the dialog box.\par \qc {\fs30\cf12 This help file was produced using the shareware version of helpMATIC V1.0}
