You first have to create a new alias and assign it to your file. Then include your file with this alias into the circuit.\par
Further descriptions are in the chapter Use in Element files.\par
\par
\qc \f1\fs32 \b The index and compatible element files\b0 \par
\ql \f0\fs24 The index of an element has to be unequivocal in the element file.\par
If two element files shall be compatible, e.g. they can be included with the same alias name in the\par
dialog box element files, corresponding elements must have the same index. The names don't have to\par
be the same. The graphic, region and the position of the inputs/outputs also don't have to be the\par
same. The element type also doesn't matter.\par
Only the index and the number of inputs/outputs has to be the same.\par \qc {\fs30\cf12 This help file was produced using the shareware version of helpMATIC V1.0}
